         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">13/1/82 ¶  ¶ What sad news, noble friend, that of the death of my dear, precious self-sacrificing friend Sonder! ¶  It is to me as if the single strong thread which connected me to the plant science o...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">82.01.13</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Ferdinand von Krauss</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Staatliches Museum für Naturkunde, Stuttgart.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by Krauss: 'Empf. 27. II Rep. 25. Apr. 82 20. Juni Wegen d. Namens des Regenwurm von McCoy gebeten' [Received 27 February Replied 25 April 82 20 June on account of asking name of McCoy's earthworm].</p>
               </note>13/1/82</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Welch' eine Trauer Botschaft, edler Freund, die des Todes meines lieben, theueren aufopfernden Freundes Sonder! Es ist mir, als ob der einzige starke Faden, der mich an die Pflanzenwissenschaft Europa’s knüpfte, zerissen wäre.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich kann es noch gar nicht realisiren, dass er, der Freund aus meiner ersten Jugendzeit, der <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Vertraute</hi>
               </seg> durch ⅓ Jahrhundert, dahingeschieden sei. Nach dem trauervollen Briefe seiner jammernden Wittwe, den ich heute von hier vorläufig durch ein Condolenz-Telegramm beantwortete, phantasirte er in den Fieberträumen seiner 4tägigen Krankheit noch immer über jüngst von mir gesandten Algen, an denen er noch arbeitete, während der Arme schon unwohl war. Den <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">letzten</hi>
               </seg> von ihm geschriebenen Brief hatte er an <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">mich</hi>
               </seg> gerichtet.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Auch <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Sie</hi>
               </seg> werden den biedern, umsichtsvollen u. zuverlässigen Freund vermissen! Wie gütig beförderte er Alles an Sie, u. doch hat er <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">nie</hi>
               </seg> selbst <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Vortheile</hi>
               </seg> davon gehabt! Es ist mir, als ob mit seinem Hintritt ich das le[tzte] Interesse am Leben verloren hätte, <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">so</hi>
               </seg> nahe standen sich unsere Gemüther!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wohl mag ich von ihm aus dem Trauer-Liede sagen:</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Das</hi>
               </seg> war ein Mann, ja nach der <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">rechten</hi>
               </seg> Art,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Gedenk ich sein, da rinnt die Thrän' mir in den Bart!<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">A misquotation of </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.5909in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Das war ein Mann von Stahl, ein Mann von echter Art </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.5909in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Gedenk ich seiner, rinnt mir die Thrän in den Bart. </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'Der Trompeter' (Kopisch), set to music by, among others, Wilhelm Speyer (see <ref target="https://nbn-resolving.org/urn:nbn:de:bvb:70-dtl-0000001225"
                          rend="Internet%20link"
                          style="color: #0563c1; ">
                        <seg rend="Internet%20link" style="color: #0563c1; ">
                           <seg style="color: #000000; ">
                              <hi rend="underline">https://nbn-resolving.org/urn:nbn:de:bvb:70-dtl-0000001225</hi>
                           </seg>
                        </seg>
                     </ref> (accessed 23 February 2021)).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wie es mit der Vermittlung des Sendens künftiger Sammlungen für Sie in Hamburg werden soll, weiss ich noch nicht.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Behüte Sie Gott vor Krankheit und anderem Unglück, das ist der Wunsch Ihres Sie Ehrenden </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Würden Sie so freundlich sein mir für meine neue Abhandlung über austral. Cycadeen <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">denjenigen</hi>
               </seg> Theil der "illustrirten Garten-Zeitung" der Gartenbau Gesellschaft <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Flora</hi>
               </seg> in Stuttgart zu senden aus dem Jahre <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">1878</hi>
               </seg> (XXII Jahrgang), welcher (ich <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">glaube</hi>
               </seg> p. 49, tab 9) eine Beschreibung und Illustration der Macrozamia Mackenziei enthält. Sie würden […]<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">An unknown amount of text missing. MS annotation with the postcript: 'z. Brief v. 13/1 82' [with letter of 13 January 1882].</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">13/1/82</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>What sad news, noble friend, that of the death of my dear, precious self-sacrificing friend Sonder!<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Sonder died on 21 November 1881.</p>
               </note> It is to me as if the single strong thread which connected me to the plant science of Europe were broken.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I cannot yet quite realise it, that he, the friend from my first youth, the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">confidant</hi>
               </seg> through a third of a century, has departed this world. According to the sad letter of his grieving widow, which I answered today from here by a telegram of condolence,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Neither letter nor telegram has been found.</p>
               </note> he fantasized in the feverish dreams of his 4-day illness always about the algae recently sent by me, on which he still worked whilst the poor man was already unwell. He had directed the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">last</hi>
               </seg> letter written by him to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">me</hi>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">You</hi>
               </seg> too will miss the honest, prudent and trustworthy friend! How kindly he dispatched everything to you, and yet he <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">never</hi>
               </seg> has had <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">profit</hi>
               </seg> from it himself! It is to me as if with his departure I had lost the last interest in life, our minds stood <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">so</hi>
               </seg> close!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Well may I say of him from the song of mourning:</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">That</hi>
               </seg> was a man, indeed of the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">right</hi>
               </seg> kind,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When I remember him, then my tears run in my beard!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I do not know yet, how it is to be in Hamburg with the arrangement for sending future collections for you.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>God protect you from illness and other accidents, that is the wish of your respectful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Would you be so kind as to send me for my new paper on Australian cycads, <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">that</hi>
               </seg> part of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Illustrirten Garten-Zeitung</seg> of the horticultural society <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Flora</hi>
               </seg> in Stuttgart from the year <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">1878</hi>
               </seg> (XXII annual) which contains (I <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">believe</hi>
               </seg> p. 49, plate 9) a description and illustration of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Macrozamia Mackenziei</seg>.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M. mackenzii? The description is very brief; it had previously been described in Masters (1877). The figure in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Illustrirten Garten-Zeitung</seg> is the same as Fig. 109 in Masters.</p>
               </note> You will […]<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">An unknown amount of text missing.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Macrozamia Mackenziei</seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
